2. Personal Use
- Personal use of versions officially released by the Owner is permitted, as long as the source code is not modified.
- Any creation of derivative works or alterations requires explicit written permission from the Owner.

3. Commercial Use
- Commercial use is strictly forbidden unless authorized via a formal written agreement with the Owner.
- If granted, such agreement must define the Owner’s share and supervisory rights in the distribution process.

4. Attribution Requirement
- When permission is granted to use or incorporate the source code, clear and visible attribution to the Owner is required, including a direct link to the original source.
- Omitting, hiding, or misrepresenting the Owner's authorship is strictly prohibited.

5. No Redistribution Without Permission
- Redistribution of any part of the source code, binaries, or modified versions is forbidden without explicit, written consent from the Owner.
- This includes unchanged, minified, modified, or repackaged versions.

6. Open Source Integrity
- The software must remain open source under this license.
- It is forbidden to “close” the source, even when adding or modifying code. The full source must always be accessible under this license.

7. Corporate Distribution
- Corporate or institutional use requires a formal distribution contract with the Owner.
- The Owner shall retain oversight and define any terms including licensing fees, revenue shares, support conditions, and limitations.

8. Violation and Legal Action
- Any breach of this license—such as unauthorized use, closed-source distribution, or commercial exploitation—may result in legal action.
- The Owner reserves the right to enforce this license through applicable domestic or international legal systems.

9. Governing Law
